## 9. Advertiser Profitability Analysis

```sql
SELECT
    advertiser_name,
    ROUND(SUM(actual_revenue), 2) AS revenue,
    ROUND(SUM(ad_spend) + SUM(cost_of_service), 2) AS total_cost,
    ROUND(SUM(actual_revenue) - (SUM(ad_spend) + SUM(cost_of_service)), 2) AS gross_profit,
    ROUND(
        (SUM(actual_revenue) - (SUM(ad_spend) + SUM(cost_of_service)))
        / NULLIF(SUM(actual_revenue), 0) * 100,
        2
    ) AS gross_margin_pct
FROM fact_ads_perf
GROUP BY advertiser_name
ORDER BY gross_profit DESC;
```

**Explanation:**
This identifies which advertisers generate the most revenue and gross profit. Since margins are relatively consistent, 
profit contribution is mainly driven by revenue scale.

