## 20. Monthly Revenue Trend with Month-over-Month Change

```sql
WITH monthly_revenue AS (
    SELECT
        year,
        month,
        MIN(month_date) AS month_date,
        ROUND(SUM(actual_revenue), 2) AS revenue
    FROM fact_ads_perf
    GROUP BY year, month
)
SELECT
    year,
    month,
    revenue,
    LAG(revenue) OVER (
        ORDER BY month_date
    ) AS previous_month_revenue,
    ROUND(
        revenue - LAG(revenue) OVER (ORDER BY month_date),
        2
    ) AS mom_revenue_change,
    ROUND(
        (revenue - LAG(revenue) OVER (ORDER BY month_date))
        / NULLIF(LAG(revenue) OVER (ORDER BY month_date), 0) * 100,
        2
    ) AS mom_growth_pct
FROM monthly_revenue
ORDER BY month_date;
```

**Explanation:**
This uses a CTE and `LAG()` window function to compare each month’s revenue against the previous month and calculate 
month-over-month growth.

